This thread of studies and anecdotes my friend compiled like 4 years ago is still the most underdiscussed fitness idea today. Arguing that detraining for 10-12 days (up to 2-3 weeks) every few months "sensitizes" muscles to exercise again and leads to increased gym muscle growth.

This lifting philosophy sorta came back now with zoomer Mike Mentzer shilling but this is probably a very sensible way to go about it. Like two weeks just going on a sea/mountain vacation, catching up on reading, etc. and you come back and get first time lifter gains for a bit.

Lindyfit is probably one of the best contrarians of all time here, used to argue for rice and orange juice sugar diet for weight loss years ago and how sugar was the best fuel for exercise, shilled detraining and low frequency training before Mentzer became big. Years ahead of us
